{{Youmay|the HoloNet News from the ''[[Star Wars Insider]]'' magazine|[[HoloNet News (disambiguation)|other meanings]]}}
'''''Republic HoloNet News''''', featured in ''[[Star Wars Insider]]'' magazine, is a series of in-universe news articles detailing galactic events during the [[Clone Wars/Legends|Clone Wars]]. The articles are written by [[Pablo Hidalgo]]. Holonet News articles were published in ''[[Star Wars Insider]]'' issues #65 to #76, after the release of [[Star Wars: Episode II Attack of the Clones|''Star Wars'': Episode II ''Attack of the Clones'']].

According to Hidalgo, the articles stopped due to the complexity involved in navigating the amount of Clone Wars-era content being produced, and because real-world news reports were detailing real wars.<ref name="Star Wars Q&A">{{InsiderCite|91|Star Wars Q&A|Ask the Master}}</ref> However, Holonet News articles returned to the ''Insider'' in issue #84, detailing the events immediately after the formation of the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]] (by [[Daniel Wallace]] and [[Pablo Hidalgo]]). According to Wallace on the [[Dark Horse Comics|Dark Horse]] boards, they wished to continue the series as [[Imperial HoloVision]], but the new Insider leadership decided against it.

